      "content": "You can take clarithromycin and simvastatin together, but you must stop the statin for 2 weeks after finishing the antibiotic to prevent dangerous muscle damage. Clarithromycin inhibits the liver enzymes that break down simvastatin, causing toxic levels to build up in your system. Since you are taking a high-risk combination, you should consult your doctor immediately to adjust your dosage or switch medications.",
